Di sini btuh ada Non-halal station juga, jadi buat yg muslim hati-hati ya salah masuk ke area non halal (mereka terpisah gitu sih). Terus pembayaran di sini juga bisa cashless pake qris gitu selain cash ya tentunya. Ikan-ikan lautnya juga seger seger.
review_translated_text: I shop here very often, almost every week. Always like it because the vegetables are really fresh. In terms of price, its a bit more expensive than traditional markets, but its okay, the vegetables are fresh, hahaha. There needs to be a non-halal station here too, so for Muslims, be careful if you enter the wrong non-halal area (they are separated like that). Then payments here can also be cashless using QRIS, apart from cash, of course. The sea fish is also fresh.

review_text: Pasar Modern BSD City, located in South Tangerang, Indonesia, offers a vibrant shopping experience that blends traditional market vibes with modern conveniences. This marketplace is particularly noted for its wide range of products, including fresh produce, local delicacies, and international foods, groceries, fruit, fish, halal and haram meat, providing a unique shopping experience for visitors. The markets lively atmosphere and modern facilities complete with variety of goods, snack and food sold in the small stalls scattered throughout this market. Its a great place to find everything from daily necessities to specialty items. However, detailed information about opening hours or any entrance access and parking isnt readily available, so it might be wise to check ahead before planning a visit. Parking in the market complex is sometime limited; if it is full, we can use paid street parking on the side of the road along the perimeter of complex.

Mungkin bisa dipikirkan penanganan lain agar pengunjung lebih nyaman dan gak was2 makanan or minuman di lalerin. 3. Daun berguguran ke meja tempat kami  makan. Untungnya pesan nasi goreng. review_translated_text: I want to give 5 stars but there are still things that need to be improved: 1. I think the concept of a shady restaurant will be in line with the eco green concept. I was really surprised when the drink came in plastic packaging, even though if you look at the reviews on YouTube, everyone was given a glass. Come on, how hard is it to wash glasses? Then after looking at it, it turns out to be expensive compared to the price. 2. Lots of big green flies! There are candles on every table but they dont seem to be able to ward off the large number of flies. Maybe you can think about other treatments so that visitors are more comfortable and dont worry about food or drinks being thrown out. 3. Leaves fell onto the table where we ate. Luckily I ordered fried rice. If its in soup its definitely going to be really annoying. The suggestion is to install a net cloth. 4. Food portions honestly agree with other reviewers that the portions are too small. You can add it to make it more palatable to eat. 5. Make sure that when plating, any other traces are wiped off. So that it doesnt seem dirty when giving it to consumers. The taste of the food is just delicious, overpriced, not really impressive. Hopefully it reaches Kondre and can be repaired. The potential is really big for this Kondre stall.

The venue is quite spacious with modest decor. As a result, I ordered the flagship menu, namely Bangladeshi Noodles. Quite tasty but not according to my expectations in other words pricy. The positive value is in the good service. The waiter was communicative and orders came quickly. Overall, worth it? I doubt it.

review_text: Datang pagi-pagi pas jam buka, menu yang available sudah cukup lengkap, sayangnya canai dan martabak belum ready karena adonannya masih beku. Lontong medan rasanya memuaskan, nasi gurih berasa rempahnya dan telur dadarnya fresh (kayaknya baru digoreng karena masih pagi), mie banglades rasanya biasa saja (sepertinya karena di rumah sering bikin pakai bumbu asli dari Aceh). Teh tariknya mantap, dan waktu menunggunya reasonable (tidak cepat namun tidak lama juga). Suasana mirip warung kopi di aceh, kalo siang sepertinya akan panas karena di area terbuka dan hanya ada kipas angin. Overall senang dengan makanan dan layanannya, dan akan kembali lagi untuk mencoba menu yang lain.
review_translated_text: Come early in the morning at opening time, the menu available is quite complete, unfortunately the canai and martabak are not ready yet because the dough is still frozen. Lontong Medan tastes satisfying, the rice tastes delicious with spices and the omelet is fresh (it looks like its just been fried because its still early), the Bangladeshi noodles taste normal (apparently because I often make them at home using authentic spices from Aceh). The Teh Tarik is great, and the waiting time is reasonable (not fast but not long either). The atmosphere is similar to a coffee shop in Aceh, during the day it seems like it will be hot because it is in an open area and there are only fans. Overall happy with the food and service, and will come back again to try other menu items.

Menjelang malam tahun baru, Serba Food pasang LIVE MUSIC di bagian outdoor. Suasananya masi sama, tetep comfy buat nongki bareng keluarga dan temen-temen. Pelayanannya oke dan ramah. . Ai pesen: Sapi Hotplate Mongolia Satu kata: ENAAAAK! Dagingnya juicy, teksturnya lembut banget dan ga nge-lawan pas dikunyah. Warbiasah! Bumbu lada hitam berasa banget, nge-blend dengan sempurna dengan potongan bawang bombaynya. Porsiannya lumayan banyak. . Pakcoy 2 Rasa Ini ga kalah makyusnya, selalu REPEAT ORDER! Daun Pakcoynya bisa se-renyah itu dan rasanya gurih. Batang Pakcoynya pun manis dan lembut. Wajib pesen kalau makan disini . Gurame Telor Asin Pilihnya bagian tengah ke ekor. Gorengnya bagus, ga oily. Bagian luarnya renyah dan daging guramenya lembut, ga amis, serta wangi daun jeruknya. Saus telor asinnya juga enak, rasa asinnya PAS. Dalam satu pax, dapet nasi, salad, potongan gurame telor asin dan kuah telor. Kuah telornya lumayan tasty. . Ayam Lady Boy Katanya ayamnya digoreng dulu baru dipanggang. Kulitnya renyah dan daging ayamnya empuk. Bisa pilih bagian dada atau paha. Satu porsi, dapet nasi, sambel, telor dadar, ayam dan kuah bening. Lumayan lah ga seret jadinya hehehe. . Lemongrass Ice Tea Teh serehnya enak, wangi serehnya kerasa banget. Nikmat. . Tahu Enoki (Rp 40K) Tahunya dicampur dengan jamur enoki lembut dan kuah coklatnya enak. Suka banget! Satu porsi isi 4 potong tahu lumutnya dan ada potongan pakcoy. . Ayam Ibu Tiri (Rp 60K) Seperti ayam cabe lada garam. Ayam fillet dipotong memanjang dan digoreng tepung. Ada campuran kacang, potongan cabe dan daun bawang. Rasanya gurih dan teksturnya empuk. Cuman kurang nampol aja bumbunya dan kurang tercampur dengan baik lada garamnya. Didominasi dengan rasa pedas lada. . Tahu Telor Asin (Rp 45K) Kesan pertama enak dan gurih tapi kalau kebanyakan agak mabok dan eneg juga. Renyah dan saus telor asinnya berasa banget. Ada potongan cabe merahnya dan agak pedas. . Onde Naiwong Pandan (Rp 28K) My favorite! Satu porsi isi 3 bulatan dan disajikan masih panas. Bentuknya lumayan besar dengan isian kacang ijo yang sudah dilembutkan. Renyah di luar dan enak pas digigit! . Es Teh Tawar (Rp 10K) : ga bisa REFILL gaes!
review_translated_text: Towards New Years Eve, Serba Food put on LIVE MUSIC in the outdoor section. The atmosphere is still the same, its still comfortable for hanging out with family and friends. The service is okay and friendly. . Ai messaged: Mongolian Hotplate Beef One word: ENAAAAK! The meat is juicy, the texture is very soft and doesnt resist when chewed. Be wary! The black pepper seasoning is really delicious, it blends perfectly with the chopped onions. The portion is quite large. . Pakchoy 2 Flavors This is no less important, always REPEAT ORDER! Pakcoy leaves can be that crunchy and taste delicious. The Pakchoy stems are also sweet and soft. You must order if you eat here . Salted Egg Gurami Select the middle part to the tail. The frying is good, not oily. The outside is crispy and the gourami meat is soft, not fishy, and smells good of lime leaves. The salted egg sauce is also delicious, the salty taste is PERFECT. In one pax, you get rice, salad, pieces of salted egg gourami and egg sauce. The egg soup is quite tasty. . Lady Boy Chicken They say the chicken is fried first and then grilled. The skin is crispy and the chicken meat is tender. You can choose the chest or thighs. One portion, get rice, chili sauce, omelette, chicken and clear sauce. Its not bad that it doesnt drag, hehehe. . Lemongrass Ice Tea The lemongrass tea is delicious, the lemongrass smells really good. Enjoyment. . Enoki Tofu (Rp. 40K) The tofu is mixed with soft enoki mushrooms and the chocolate sauce is delicious. Really like! One portion contains 4 pieces of moss tofu and pieces of pak choy. . Stepmothers Chicken (Rp. 60K) Like salt pepper chili chicken. Chicken fillet is cut lengthwise and fried in flour. There is a mixture of nuts, chopped chilies and spring onions. The taste is delicious and the texture is soft. Its just that the seasoning isnt enough and the salt and pepper arent mixed well. Dominated by the spicy taste of pepper. . Salted Egg Tofu (Rp. 45K) The first impression is that it is delicious and tasty, but if you eat too much, its a bit drunk and uncomfortable too. Its crunchy and the salted egg sauce really tastes good. There are pieces of red chili and its a bit spicy. . Onde Naiwong Pandan (Rp. 28K) My favourite! One portion contains 3 circles and is served still hot. The shape is quite large and filled with softened green beans. Crispy on the outside and delicious when you bite into it! . Fresh Iced Tea (Rp. 10K): cant REFILL, guys!

review_text: Tempatnya oke dan instagrammable. Suasananya asyik dengan latar musik. Makanan dan minumannya enak2. Saya udah 3 kali ke sini. Pertama, waktu kafenya baru buka. Waktu itu makan malam sama teman2. Suasananya rame.  Kedua, akhir tahun lalu sore2 ngopi sama teman. Suasanya sepi. Ketiga, awal bulan ini makan siang sama teman2 dari Jakarta. Cukup rame. Cuma saya kurang cocok sama nasi goreng yg pake nanas. Saya lebih suka yg gurih. Oh, ya, ada semacam teh rempah yg unik--love potion--yg diminum di cangkir yg superimut. Uang yg saya keluarkan beda2 jumlahnya karena saya juga pesannya beda2.
review_translated_text: The place is okay and instagrammable. The atmosphere is fun with background music. The food and drinks are delicious. Ive been here 3 times. First, when the cafe just opened. It was dinner time with friends. The atmosphere is lively. Second, at the end of last year I had coffee with friends in the afternoon. The atmosphere is quiet. Third, earlier this month I had lunch with friends from Jakarta. Quite busy. I just dont like fried rice that uses pineapple. I prefer savory ones. Oh, yes, there is a unique kind of spiced tea--love potion--which is drunk in super cute cups. The amount of money I spent was different because I also ordered different amounts.

review_text: Coffe lokasi strategis biasa sore pulang kantor sekedar meeting kecil atau hanya rehat. Rasa coffee standar, rekomendasi macha dan makanan kecil ubi. review_translated_text: Coffee in a strategic location, usually in the afternoon after work for a small meeting or just taking a break. Standard coffee taste, recommended macha and sweet potato snacks. The atmosphere can be while watching the traffic while doing homework. The ablution and prayer room is available on the 2nd floor, the bathroom is quite clean. Parking is also still free. Close to home so you can go directly to a gojek/gocar. The place is comfortable enough to work and can be close to an electrical contact for charging the laptop. Usually in the afternoon and evening the atmosphere is dynamic with views of the Kencana Loka T-junction.

review_text: Mampir karena kebetulan hujan, jadi melipir dan memutuskan untuk berteduh sejenak disini. Kopi kenangan sepertinya sama semua di setiap kedai ya. Burgernya tidak sesuai di gambar, dagingnya tipis, sangat kering masaknya jadinya agak keras ketika dimakan, kebantu sama sausnya saja jadi bisa di makan. Isinya cuma caramelized onion, daging sama sausnya. Sangat diluar ekspetasi gambar yang ditampilkan. Bonelessnya juicy namun tepungnya agak keras sih. Lupa foto karna ribet abis kehujanan. Terimakasih
review_translated_text: Stopped by because it happened to be raining, so pulled over and decided to take shelter for a moment here. Memories of coffee seem to be the same in every shop, right? If its Chigo The burger didnt look like the picture, the meat was thin, very dry and cooked so it was a bit tough when eaten, the sauce helped so it could be eaten. It only contains caramelized onions, meat and sauce. Very beyond the expectations of the picture shown. The boneless is juicy but the flour is a bit hard. Forgot to take a photo because it was complicated after being caught in the rain. Thank You

review_text: jadi ceritanya saya abis makan di salah satu tempat di dekay coffee ya, namun karna belum terlalu malam akhir ya saya mencari tempat coffee di sekitar tempat saya makan, akhirnya saya menemukan coffee ya dengan rating yang lumayan banyak dan dari ulasan yang banyak juga setelah saya sampai, saya memesan ice matcha dan hot cappuccino. namun setelah saya melakuan pesanan dan beberapa menit kemudian pesanan saya datang. nah di sini, semua di luar ekspetasi saya kok gini ice matchanya (rasanya apek) entah dari powdernya udah lama atau gimana saya ga tau deh dan untuk cappuccino nya sendiri pait parah, saya berasumsi apakah menggunakan beans full robusta yang di roasting full dark atau dari si baristanya yang bikin espressonya over ekstrak, tapi ya udah lah masih bisa di minum yang jadi ya gimana lagi ya, agak kureng yakin aja sama ratingnya yg lumayan
response_from_owner_text: Hi buddy. Thanks for the review and sorry for your experience. Its weird because we usually get lots of compliments for our matcha drink. Dan untuk latte original dan cappucino, kita pakai housblend arabica fresh(1, maximal 2 weeks sittings) dan bukan robusta beans. And again, no one ever complain about the taste of our arabica beans. We will investige of this case for sure. :) Anyway, if you ever come back, please let our barista knows about this and your next bitter coffee will be on us. Haha
review_translated_text: So the story is that I just finished eating at one of the places near Coffee, but because it wasnt too late, I looked for a coffee place near where I was eating, finally I found a coffee with quite a lot of ratings and lots of reviews too. after I arrived, I ordered iced matcha and hot cappuccino. but after I placed my order and a few minutes later my order came. well here, everything is beyond my expectations Why is the matcha ice like this (it tastes musty) whether the powder has been there for a long time or what, I dont know... and the cappuccino itself is really bad, Im assuming whether it uses full robusta beans that are roasted fully dark or from the barista who makes the espresso with over extract, but yes, its still drinkable. So what else can I do, Im a bit unsure of how good the rating will be

review_text: cukup sekali aja kesini, gak lagi2 deh. sangat tidak rekomen. salah serve dan harus bayar, double serve, dan makanan blm di serve tapi sudah di checklist wkwk kocak sih. bukber yang lalu pilih tempat ini karna estetik, kami booking untuk 5 pax. sebelum sampe tempatnya kami ditelfon karna kesorean mba makanannya kami sajikan ya, karna sudah menjelang magrib oke. pas sampe disana ternyata baru 3 yang disajikan, ada kolak dan salad (saya pikir oh mungkin ini welcome food edisi ramadhan karna lihat di ig storynya), saya pesan lagi untuk 1 org yang belum pesan, jadi total kami 6 orang kesini. sudah magrib, baru 5 orang yang disajikan termasuk yang baru pesan. satu orang dari menu pas booking belum disajikan. ada kali 10x manggil waiters buat ingetin . akhirnya temenku ini makan saladnya, pas lagi bete2nya makan makanan gaenak eh waiters dateng ngitung bill, yg pertama ternyata bukan bill kami, yang kedua mastiin pesenan ternyata kita gada pesan salad tp dicatatan dia ada akhirnya bayarlah kami, dateng lagi waiters lain buat mastiin makanan sdh disajikan semua atau belum ternyata yang 1 itu belum disajikan juga (ni sampe dateng 2x tp blm disajiin jg), datang lagi yang bawa bill masih salah pesanan lagi. tolong lah ini kalo codeblue yang dateng udah abis kalian wkwk. cuma 6 pax udah seruwet ini. ohiya, pas mau pulang tiba2 kami disajikan lagi dongg, yang dimana pesanan itu udah disajikan dan udah abis bahkan meja udah bersih wkwk. kasian ownernya, ambience oke bgt estetik. tapi manajemen dan pelayanannya butuh diperbaiki, sangat butuh. padahal ada tarif pelayanan, ya. untuk harga makanan dan pelayanannya sangat tidak worth it hehe.
review_translated_text: Its enough just to come here once, not again. really dont recommend. wrong service and have to pay, double serve, and the food hasnt been served yet but its already on the checklist, its hilarious. Last time we chose this place because of its aesthetics, we booked for 5 pax. Before arriving at the place we got a call because it was late afternoon Maam, well serve the food, because its approaching sunset okay. When I got there, it turned out that only 3 had been served, there was compote and salad (I thought oh maybe this is the Ramadhan edition of welcome food because I saw the IG story), I ordered more for 1 person who hadnt ordered, so a total of 6 of us came here. It was already sunset, only 5 people had been served including those who had just ordered. one person from the menu when booking has not been served. I called the waiters 10 times to remind you  . Finally my friend ate the salad, just when he was feeling nervous about eating the food, the waiter came to count the bill, the first time it turned out it wasnt our bill, the second time he confirmed the order, it turned out we didnt order the salad but he noted that he finally paid us, another waiter came again to make sure the food was ready. Was it all served or not? It turned out that the first one hadnt been served either (this arrived twice but it hadnt been served yet), when the bill came again, the order was still wrong. Please help if the codeblue that arrived has run out, hahaha. only 6 pax, its already so complicated. Oh yeah, when we were about to go home, we were suddenly served again, where the order had already been served and was finished and the table was already clean, wow. poor owner, the ambience is very aesthetically pleasing. but the management and service need to be improved, really need it. even though there is a service fee, yes. for the price of the food and service its not really worth it hehe.

review_translated_text: The most worth it cafe during my visits to cafes in South Tangerang! In terms of price, service, and ambience, it is almost perfect. Baristas, waiters, et al are very friendly. Found this hidden gem in July and until now, if I want to hang out/work on assignments/do work, I always go here because it feels homey It has 2 floors, the concept is semi-outdoor but its still cool because there are lots of trees around the cafe. But on the 2nd floor, if the night is a bit dim, the lights are better on the 1st floor. The food is relatively affordable and the portions are large. Ive tried all the food menus, almost all of them are delicious but the spaghetti isnt al dente enough and doesnt have enough seasoning hehe (its okay for future input). FYI, this cafe has a loyalty card so if you have all the stamps, you can exchange them and get a free snack of your choice. And now I have a third loyalty card while Ive been here because I come so often haha   Oh yes, you can also paint here with a minimum purchase of 80 thousand (canvas, paint, brushes and palettes are provided). Shout out to Aldilah, Noval, et al, their service is top notch and is the best!!!!

Berkeliling di daerah lebak bulus, rempoa, dan ciputat mencari kulineran yang mau dicoba bersama keluarga dengan tempat yang luas dan nyaman bisa dicoba resto ini. Saya mendapatkan di google maps yaitu Temu Rasa. Ternyata saat sampai di lokasi ada beberapa jenis mau cafe ada dan resto juga ada. Parkiran mobil dan motor aman karena lumayan bisa menampung banyak kendaraan. Resto ini menyediakan beberapa lantai yang terbagi jadi dua, yaitu indoor (ac atau non ac) dan outdoor yang kalau bawa keluarga bisa main di halaman rumput sambil menyantap makanan. Untuk cafe dan restonya ada pilihan berbagai macam kopi dan cemilan apabila mau sambil kerja/meeting atau bersama keluarga dengan hidangan makanan khas western, asia dan indonesia. Banyak spot foto yang bagus di tempat makan ini dan kalau malam sejuk hembusan anginnya. Dan staf-stafnya sigap serta ramah apabila ada pertanyaan-pertanyaan yang mau ditanyakan. Kid-friendliness: Halaman luas
review_translated_text: Traveling around the Lebak Bulus, Rempoa and Ciputat areas looking for culinary delights that you want to try with your family in a spacious and comfortable place, you can try this restaurant. I found it on Google Maps, namely Temu Rasa. It turned out that when we arrived at the location there were several types of cafes and restaurants too. Parking for cars and motorbikes is safe because it can accommodate quite a lot of vehicles. This restaurant provides several floors which are divided into two, namely indoor (ac or non-ac) and outdoor, so if you bring your family you can play on the lawn while eating food. For cafes and restaurants, there is a choice of various kinds of coffee and snacks if you want while working/meeting or with your family with typical western, Asian and Indonesian dishes. There are lots of good photo spots at this eating place and the wind blows cool at night. And the staff are alert and friendly if you have questions. Kid-friendliness: Spacious yard

review_text: Berada dalam area taman wisata situ gintung, lokasi mudah ditemukan karena dekat dari pintu utama taman wisata. Tersedia parkir kendaraan roda empat dan roda dua. Sesuai namanya kafe berada di atas dengan desain cozy dan nyaman. Ada tempat spot untuk live music diwaktu tertentu. Ada jg spot tempat bermain anak seperti tamia dan uno. Pilihan makanan dan minuman bervariasi dengan harga terjangkau. Coffe dan non-coffe tersedia disini yang disajikan oleh pramusaji & barista yang ramah dan baik. Recommended Es Susu Di Atas dan Cireng Rujak. Favorite Mie ayam, really delicious. Belum tersedia wifi dan ruang ber-AC.
review_translated_text: Located in the Situ Gintung tourist park area, the location is easy to find because it is close to the main gate of the tourist park. Parking for four-wheeled and two-wheeled vehicles is available. As the name suggests, the cafe is at the top with a cozy and comfortable design. There are spots for live music at certain times. There are also childrens play spots such as Tamia and Uno. Varied food and drink choices at affordable prices. Coffee and non-coffee are available here which are served by friendly and kind waiters & baristas. Recommended Ice Milk Above and Cireng Rujak. Favorite Chicken noodles, really delicious. WiFi and air-conditioned rooms are not yet available.

review_text: Tempat nongkrong disekitar komplek UIN. Lokasinya mojok banget dan ada di lantai atas. Pertama kali kesini pas hari Minggu berharap bisa nonton live musicnya, tapi sayang ngga ada. Kurang tau apa karena ga ada jadwal atau karena kondisi kafe yg sepi (kebetulan saat itu cm ada meja gue, mbak-mbak berdua dan segerombolan orang reuni kayanya yg sudah pulang lebih dahulu). Cuma ada mas-mas jamming(bener ga sih istilahnya?) gitar listrik aja yg ternyata dia asik banget mainnya, jd lumayan menghibur hehe. Untuk menu lumayan variatif dan terjangkau. Trus pas udah agak malem sisa meja gue doang, tiba-tiba dikasih kentang goreng dong, compliment katanya haha makasih ya mas! Bakal balik lagi kok, aku masih nungguin live musicnya pokoknya!
review_translated_text: Hangout place around the UIN complex. The location is really corner and is on the top floor. The first time I came here was on a Sunday hoping to see live music, but unfortunately there wasnt any. I dont know whether it was because there was no schedule or because the cafe was quiet (it just so happened that at that time there was my table, the two of you and a group of rich reunion people who had gone home earlier). There were only guys jamming (is that the correct term?) on electric guitar which turned out to be really fun to play, so it was quite entertaining hehe. The menu is quite varied and affordable. Then, when it was a little late, I was the only one left on the table, suddenly I was given French fries, compliments, he said, haha, thanks, bro! Ill be back again, Im still waiting for the live music!

review_translated_text: wedang uwuh oolong tea IDR: 36,000 . This is tea mixed with traditional spices. This time, request a lot of ginger (but if you dont really like ginger, you can request just a little). the taste really makes your throat feel good, especially since the ginger tastes really spicy. must try! salted caramel crackers IDR: 38,000 . Those who dont really like very strong coffee must try the salted caramel. the combination is just right and not too sweet. so delicious   . There are also pieces of biscuit on top too. Gong Fu Cha White Tea. When I came here I was offered white tea. Drinking tea on a rainy day is really the best here. There are also lots of tea variants and if you come here just chat with the owner who is super kind and friendly.

review_text: Sudah cukup lama menjadi customer Dela, dari yang tadinya di Sekbil Bintaro dan sekarang di Serua Ciputat. Untuk tempat yang dulu 3 lantai sekarang jadi 2 lantai, tapi lantai 2 sudah termasuk indoor dan outdoor. Lantai 1 sangat nyaman untuk bersantai, sofanya enak banget. Lantai 2 indoor lebih cocok untuk WFC, tapi sayangnya agak panas, kursinya agak bikin pegal, dan beberapa mejanya kekecilan. Lantai 3 outdoor enak buat nongkrong ataupun WFC. Disini parkirannya luas, juga tersedia musola dan toilet yang nyaman. Untuk varian menu baik itu main course, minuman, dan kudapan masih sama ya, tapi ada beberapa varian baru sekarang. Dari dulu sampai sekarang yang stand out dari cafe ini menurut gue justru makanannya, harus dicoba pizza dan kudapan lainnya karena enak dan porsinya banyak. review_translated_text: Have been a Dela customer for quite a long time, from previously at Sekbil Bintaro and now at Serua Ciputat. For places that used to have 3 floors, now they have 2 floors, but the 2nd floor includes indoor and outdoor. The 1st floor is very comfortable for relaxing, the sofa is really comfortable. The indoor 2nd floor is more suitable for WFC, but unfortunately its a bit hot, the chairs are a bit sore, and some of the tables are too small. The outdoor 3rd floor is good for hanging out or WFC. Here the parking is spacious, there are also prayer rooms and comfortable toilets. The menu variants, including main courses, drinks and snacks, are still the same, but there are several new variants now. From the past until now, what stands out about this cafe in my opinion is the food, you have to try the pizza and other snacks because they are delicious and the portions are large. The drinks are still quite good but not that special for me. If you compare it with the previous place, honestly I prefer the previous one. In the past, it was so comfortable to work from day to night, but now its easier to access so its okay.

review_text: I actually WANTED TO GATE KEEP THIS PLACEEE.. but i also want to help this local business thrive!! Ive been goin to this cafe for a year now (*more or less), also been comparing this cafe to other neighborhood cafe but im already hook to this cafe cannot get better cafe than this one here!. Ive given the chance to know the owner, co-owner, and daily worker here! Okay so now for Food Review~ the food is worth the price! Im not lying to you when i say This Worth the portion and price! Since its local owned they didnt have taxes like in street cafe, or restaurant. Now thats gonna relate to Service Review now~ for service its just ordinary not overly perfection, they deliver the food too but remember since they didnt have service tax so dont expect Perfection from the workers! But if you want to tip they accept tip so pls tip well! Atmosphere Review~ for the scenery its like a hidden bali cafe for me.. yes i said what i said. A hidden place with unexpected vibe and scenery! *Hi, i review this honestly as i can because i work in the same field also, no i didnt work there. I work somewhere else but i felt that this local cafe is too good to be missed out by people! Hold up one more! For vegetarian and vegan out there you can request to change some ingredients but with same price okay, make it logical babes. Once i changed uhm some rice bowl but the orginal recipe have to put chicken in it, i ask them if i can change it to 2 egg and they allow it, as long you make it logical okay!

Gak ada update info di Instagram atau di google map. Dateng jauh2 dari pancoran ternyata zonk. Padahal bisa dengan mudah kasih info kalau lagi tutup di Story instagram. Jadinya maaf saya kasih rate 1. Mohon jadikan pembelajaran kedepannya. Update informasi soal jam dan hari operasional itu sangat penting!!! Dalam sehari bisa banyak customer yang kena zonk hanya karena malas update info jam operasional.
review_translated_text: Coming here from a long way turns out to be boring. When you look at the info on Google Map, its open from 9 am to 00.00. When I arrived at half past 5 in the afternoon it turned out it was closed full day. There is no updated information on Instagram or on Google Maps. Coming far from Pancoran, it turned out to be a zone. Even though you can easily provide information if your Instagram Story is closed. So, sorry, I gave it a rating of 1. Please use it as a lesson for the future. Updating information about operational hours and days is very important!!! In one day, many customers can get zoned out just because they are lazy about updating information on operational hours.

review_text: Tidak semua tenant di dalam satu area food temptation menggunakan metode pembayaran kartu food temptation, dan juga sebaliknya, sehingga sangat membingungkan konsumen yang baru pertama kali datang, dan pada akhirnya kartu pembayaran tidak digunakan sama sekali karena beberapa tenant yang sangat ingin dikunjungi untuk dibeli makanannya menolak pembayaran menggunakan kartu food temptation yang sudah di top up sebelumnya. Konsep & kualitas tenant masih kalah jauh dibanding Futopia Alam Sutera yang dimana semua tenant di dalam satu area wajib menggunakan kartu pembayaran Futopia, sehingga orang yang pertama kali datangpun tidak langsung kebingungan.
review_translated_text: Not all tenants in one food temptation area use the food temptation card payment method, and vice versa, so it is very confusing for consumers who are coming for the first time, and in the end payment cards are not used at all because some tenants who really want to visit to buy food refuse Payment using a food temptation card that has been topped up previously. The concept & quality of tenants is still far less than Futopia Alam Sutera, where all tenants in one area are required to use Futopia payment cards, so that people who come for the first time are not immediately confused.

review_text: Harga terjangkau mulai dari Rp8.000 - Rp15.000, tersedia paket hemat, brown sugar, bubble, dan cheese boba. Bobanya terasa spesial karena manis dan pecah (popping) ketika digigit. Terakhir saya ke sana (Desember 2019) ada promo beli 2 bonus 1 (bonusnya hanya pilihan paket hemat Rp8.000). Sangat dekat dengan gapura Kampus II UIN Jakarta, kalau lewat sana ada di kanan jalannya. Kurangnya saat itu belum bisa menerima pembayaran dompet digital dan nontunai lain, semoga disegerakan. Dan foto bangunan terbaru di Google Maps belum ada, semoga tim Google Street View segera memutakhirkan.
review_translated_text: Affordable prices start from IDR 8,000 - IDR 15,000, economical packages available, brown sugar, bubble and cheese boba. The boba tastes special because it is sweet and pops when bitten. The last time I went there (December 2019) there was a buy 2 bonus 1 promotion (the bonus was only the Rp. 8,000 saving package option). Very close to the gate of Campus II UIN Jakarta, if you go through there it is on the right side of the road. At this time, we cannot accept digital wallet and other non-cash payments, hopefully this will be done soon. And there are no photos of the latest building on Google Maps yet, hopefully the Google Street View team will update it soon.

review_text: Es KODE is a legendary place to sell fresh fruit juice. Located on jl. Soleh Ali, Tangerang. You can open a google map to get to the location. Parking is quite difficult due to roadside parking around the site. Parking attendants will help direct where to park your vehicle. There are many juice menus and some ice (es campur, es teler). After ordering the drink menu, pay immediately. Once youre ready, youll be called to pick up your order, then you can sit in the space provided. The place is not as nice as the cafe in the mall, but its quite clean. You can dine in or take away. Some snacks are also available. Price : $ Since opening in 1960, Jus Kode has always been a destination for fresh fruit juice. Since some time ago, it seems to have changed its name to ES KODE (maybe there are those who open code juice in several places). There is a statement from ES KODE if it does not open branches in other places.

review_text: Sambel Hejo Sambel Dadak (SHSD) salah satu rumah makan khas sajian utama ayam goreng kampung yang sangat ueenakkk. Rasanya cukup unik digoreng tidak terlalu kering cenderung masih berminyak dimana ukuran ayam sedang dipotong potong dan tekstur empuk. Disajikan dengan sambel cabe hijau yg dibikin dadakan sangat pas taste nya yummy. Selain itu ada menu varian lainnya khas tanah pasundan ikan bakar/goreng, sate kambing, lalapan, tahu tempe goreng, ikan peda, pepesan, sayur asem dll. Tempat nya santai bernuansa klasik pendopo joglo dengan ukiran khas pasundan. Ruangan indoor full AC No Smoking Area dan tersedia juga outdoor. Namun menuju lokasi ini traffic sangat padat sehingga dibutuhkan kesabaran sampai tempat tujuan. Parkiran cukup luas namun selalu penuh. Parkir disini gratis. Recommended.
review_translated_text: Sambel Hejo Sambel Dadak (SHSD) is one of the typical restaurants with the main dish of village fried chicken which is really delicious. The taste is quite unique, fried, not too dry, tends to be oily, where the chicken is cut into medium sized pieces and the texture is tender. Served with green chili sauce which is made suddenly, it tastes delicious. Apart from that, there are other menu variants typical of Tanah Pasundan, grilled/fried fish, goat satay, fresh vegetables, fried tofu and tempeh, spicy fish, pepesan, tamarind vegetables, etc. The place is relaxed and has a classic Joglo pavilion with typical Pasundan carvings. The indoor room is fully AC, No Smoking Area and outdoor is also available. However, traffic is very busy to get to this location so you need patience to reach your destination. The parking lot is quite large but is always full. Parking here is free. Recommended.

Its a shame that a nice place like this only misses out on the service Thats all thank youuu

review_text: Located side by side with a huge mosque. Spacious parking lot, warm ambiance indoor and outdoor area, nice backyard with fish pond that make it so cozy and calm. The prices are reasonable, clean restroom, but the service was quitely slow. If we seat in the outer, its difficult to reach out the staffs. The soto betawi and garang asem are tasty but the pasta and another western menu just so-so, but all good Update: Setelah 2 tahun akhirnya balik lagi, menu indonesian foodnya makin banyak. Pesan Nasgor CDC, Kwetiauw Goreng, dan Nasi Campur Bali. Kwetiauwnya mantep banget, bumbunya medok dan berasa pedasnya (by request). Service kitchennya juga cepet. Nasgornya so-so tapi enak    Nasi Balinya porsi besar, ada sate lilitnya juga enak walaupun agak kering, ayamnya juga besar, kuah kuningnya enak   Sekarang tiap table ada service bell-nya jadi kl mau manggil staff lebih mudah. Nice improvement!
review_translated_text: Located side by side with a huge mosque. Spacious parking lot, warm ambiance indoor and outdoor area, nice backyard with fish pond that makes it so cozy and calm. The prices are reasonable, clean restroom, but the service was quite slow. If we sit in the outside, its difficult to reach out the staff. The soto betawi and garang asem are tasty but the pasta and another western menu are just so-so, but all good Updates: After 2 years, finally back again, the menu has more Indonesian food. Order Nasgor CDC, Fried Kwetiauw, and Balinese Mixed Rice. The kwetiauw is really delicious, the spices are soft and have a spicy taste (by request). The kitchen service is also fast. The Nasgor is so-so but delicious    The Balinese rice is a big portion, the satay lilit is also delicious even though its a bit dry, the chicken is also big, the yellow sauce is delicious   Now every table has a service bell so if you want to call the staff its easier. Nice improvement!

review_text: Nyantai Asyik di Tangerang Tempatnya Dekat Masjid Raya Rahmatan Lil Alamin, Tangerang. Tempatnya luas, ada indoor dan outdoor. Indoornya modern dan instagramable, outdoornya adem dan asri. Pilihannya banyak makaman, dari western sampe lokal. Ada pasta, steak, nasi goreng, mie ayam, dll. Rasanya enak dan porsinya pas. Harganya standar kafe, sekitar Rp 50.000 - Rp 100.000 per orang. Kopinya mantap! Ada berbagai pilihan kopi dan non-kopi. Ada jus, smoothies, dan mocktail juga. Cocok buat nyantai, ngobrol, atau kerja. Wifi kenceng dan colokan banyak. Ada live music di malam hari. Pelayanannya Ramah dan sigap. Overall, CdC Coffee & Eatery recommended banget buat yang nyari tempat nyantai asyik di Tangerang.
review_translated_text: Relaxing fun in Tangerang The place is near the Rahmatan Lil Alamin Grand Mosque, Tangerang. The place is spacious, there is indoor and outdoor. The indoor is modern and instagrammable, the outdoor is cool and beautiful. There are many choices of cemeteries, from western to local. There is pasta, steak, fried rice, chicken noodles, etc. It tastes delicious and the portion is just right. The price is cafe standard, around IDR 50,000 - IDR 100,000 per person. The coffee is great! There are various coffee and non-coffee options. There are juices, smoothies and mocktails too. Suitable for relaxing, chatting or working. Fast wifi and lots of plugs. There is live music at night. The service is friendly and alert. Overall, CdC Coffee & Eatery is really recommended for those looking for a fun relaxing place in Tangerang.

review_text: Salah satu mie aceh terenak se-jabodetabek yang pernah saya coba! Mmg bukan satu satunya yang terenak, tapi ini masuk ke kategori yang enak! Untuk mie acehnya saya pesan yang tumis saya beri rating 8.5/10. rasa rempahnya khas mie aceh enak berasa kental, porsinya juga pas (ga terlalu sedikit atau terlalu banyak). Dengan catatan tingkat kepedasan yang sedang juga sudah cukup pedas tapi masih bisa dinikmati! RECOMMENDED. Teh Tarik hangat saya beri rating 6/10. Menurut saya rasanya hanya manis saja, rasa teh dan susunya sangat light. Aroma tehnya pun tidak ada, aftertaste yg agak pahit dari tehnya juga tidak ada. Saya berekspektasi teh tariknya dengan aroma strong dan kental, tapi ternyata tidak sesuai ekspektasi. Saya TIDAK MEREKOMENDASIKAN dine in, karena tempatnya cukup panas dan kurangnya sirkulasi udara, jd kurang nyaman untuk makan langsung disana. Untuk yang membawa mobil juga untuk aksesnya cukup sulit, biasanya harus jalan lagi dan cari parkir di ruko2 tsb. Selain itu, semoga pelayanannya makin gercep dalam menyiapkan pesanan customer yaa.
review_translated_text: One of the tastiest Acehnese noodles in Jabodetabek that I have ever tried! Its not the tastiest one, but its in the delicious category! For the Acehnese noodles, I ordered stir-fried, I gave it a rating of 8.5/10. The spice taste is typical of Acehnese noodles, it tastes thick, the portion is just right (not too little or too much). Note that the medium level of spiciness is also quite spicy but can still be enjoyed! RECOMMENDED. I give the warm Teh Tarik a rating of 6/10. In my opinion, the taste is just sweet, the taste of tea and milk is very light. There is no aroma of the tea, there is also no slightly bitter aftertaste from the tea. I expected the Teh Tarik to have a strong and thick aroma, but it didnt meet my expectations. I DO NOT RECOMMEND dine in, because the place is quite hot and there is a lack of air circulation, so it is not comfortable to eat directly there. For those who bring cars, access is also quite difficult, usually you have to walk again and look for parking in the shophouses. Apart from that, hopefully the service will be faster in preparing customer orders.

review_text: Tempat makan mie aceh favorite sudah hampir 8 tahun ansejak semester 1 kuliah Hampir semua makanan udah pernah saya coba dan semuanya enak sesuai sama lidah saya, sempet tanya juga sama temen ku yang orang aceh asli apakah yang disana juga rasanya sama kayak yang di bungoong jeumpa dan jawaban nya sih iyaaa Favorite masih dipegang mie aceh kuah daging pedas sama teh tarik nyaa(wanginya khas banget kayaknya lake cinnamon ya) Harga menurut ku worth it dengan porsi dan juga rasa yang enak, tapi memang waktu pertama kali kesini porsinya banyak banget sekarang tetap banyak tapi gak sebanyak dulu. Untuk suasana tempat makan nya, meja dan kursinya terbatas ygy dan memang rada panas juga kalau di cabang ciputat ini, kalau mau rada luas bisa ke yang di dekat stasiun jurangmangu. Kadang juga kalau lagi antri bisa makan waktu lebih dari 1 jam walupun take away. Last kalau kalian gak terlalu suka makanan yang banyak rempah dan bumbunya nendang bingbing pikirin dulu aja atau sharing bareng temen aja dulu
review_translated_text: Favorite place to eat Acehnese noodles for almost 8 years, since the first semester of college I have tried almost all the foods and they are all delicious according to my taste buds, I also asked my friend who is a native Acehnese whether what there tastes the same as the one at Bungoong Jeumpa and the answer is yes. The favorite is still the Acehnese noodles with spicy beef soup and the Teh Tarik (the smell is really distinctive, like lake cinnamon, right) In my opinion, the price is worth it with the portions and delicious taste, but when I first came here the portions were really big, now they are still big but not as much as before. As for the dining atmosphere, the tables and chairs are limited and its also a bit hot at the Ciputat branch, if you want a bit more space, you can go to the one near Panggangmangu station. Sometimes, if youre queuing, it can take more than 1 hour, even if its take away. Lastly, if you dont really like food with a lot of spices and kicking bingbing, just think about it or share it with friends first

review_text: Ini mie Aceh terenak yang pernah saya coba dari sekian banyak warung mie aceh di pulau jawa ini. Rasa bumbunya kaya akan rempah, medok khas bumbu aceh. Pernah tinggal 9 tahun di aceh dan mie ini benar2 otentik rasanya. Bagi yang tidak suka pedas jangan coba2 pesan yang pedas, karena pedasnya memang nggak kaleng2. Satu porsi mie goreng daging aceh cukup membuat kenyang. Dagingnya enggak pelit. Sekali kesini rasanya ingin kembali lagi. Sayang tempatnya terbatas dan harus rela gantian dengan pengunjung lainnya di kala pengunjung ramai. Tempat parkir untuk roda dua lumayan memadai, tapi untuk roda 4 memang agak susah, biasanya disepanjang jalan sebrang warung, tapi tenang saja ada juru parkir yang sigap mengarahkan kendaraan anda. Jangan lupa uang parkirnya.
review_translated_text: This is the tastiest Acehnese noodle I have ever tried from the many Acehnese noodle stalls on the island of Java. The taste of the seasoning is rich in spices, medok is a typical Acehnese spice. Ive lived in Aceh for 9 years and these noodles really taste authentic. For those who dont like spicy, dont try to order spicy, because it cant be spicy. One portion of Acehnese beef fried noodles is enough to make you full. The meat is not stingy. Once youve been here youll want to come back again. Unfortunately the space is limited and you have to be willing to change with other visitors when there are lots of visitors. Parking for two wheels is quite adequate, but for four wheels it is a bit difficult, usually along the road opposite the shop, but dont worry there are parking attendants who are ready to direct your vehicle. Dont forget the parking fee.

review_text: juara porsinya banyak banget level pedes ya beneran pedes, kalo ngga suka pedes mending pilih lv sedang (itupun masih pedes) kayanya lebih pedes mie aceh versi goreng daripada tumis. toppingnya banyak <<<333 untuk rasa enak bgt, mereka kaya punya rasa khas nya sendiri. nggabisa ditemuin di tempat lain. teh tariknya enak pls tempat oke cukup bersih dan nyaman buat dine in, parkirnya aja agak sempit tapi abang parkir sangat helpful duh semua oke gimana dong, udah jadi top of mind kalo bm mi aceh
review_translated_text: champion the portions are really big The spicy level is really spicy, if you dont like spicy its better to choose medium level (and even then its still spicy) It seems like the fried version of Acehnese noodles is spicier than the stir-fried version. lots of toppings <<<333 As for the delicious taste, they seem to have their own unique taste. cant be found anywhere else. the Teh Tarik is delicious pls The place is okay, quite clean and comfortable for dine in, the parking is a bit narrow but the parking guy is very helpful oops, everything is okay, how about it, its already top of mind when it comes to BM Mi Aceh

review_text: Salah satu mie aceh terenak se-jabodetabek yang pernah saya coba! Mmg bukan satu satunya yang terenak, tapi ini masuk ke kategori yang enak! Untuk mie acehnya saya pesan yang tumis saya beri rating 8.5/10. rasa rempahnya khas mie aceh enak berasa kental, porsinya juga pas (ga terlalu sedikit atau terlalu banyak). Dengan catatan tingkat kepedasan yang sedang juga sudah cukup pedas tapi masih bisa dinikmati! RECOMMENDED. Teh Tarik hangat saya beri rating 6/10. Menurut saya rasanya hanya manis saja, rasa teh dan susunya sangat light. Aroma tehnya pun tidak ada, aftertaste yg agak pahit dari tehnya juga tidak ada. Saya berekspektasi teh tariknya dengan aroma strong dan kental, tapi ternyata tidak sesuai ekspektasi. Saya TIDAK MEREKOMENDASIKAN dine in, karena tempatnya cukup panas dan kurangnya sirkulasi udara, jd kurang nyaman untuk makan langsung disana. Untuk yang membawa mobil juga untuk aksesnya cukup sulit, biasanya harus jalan lagi dan cari parkir di ruko2 tsb. Selain itu, semoga pelayanannya makin gercep dalam menyiapkan pesanan customer yaa.
review_translated_text: One of the tastiest Acehnese noodles in Jabodetabek that I have ever tried! Its not the tastiest one, but its in the delicious category! For the Acehnese noodles, I ordered stir-fried, I gave it a rating of 8.5/10. The spice taste is typical of Acehnese noodles, it tastes thick, the portion is just right (not too little or too much). Note that the medium level of spiciness is also quite spicy but can still be enjoyed! RECOMMENDED. I give the warm Teh Tarik a rating of 6/10. In my opinion, the taste is just sweet, the taste of tea and milk is very light. There is no aroma of the tea, there is also no slightly bitter aftertaste from the tea. I expected the Teh Tarik to have a strong and thick aroma, but it didnt meet my expectations. I DO NOT RECOMMEND dine in, because the place is quite hot and there is a lack of air circulation, so it is not comfortable to eat directly there. For those who bring cars, access is also quite difficult, usually you have to walk again and look for parking in the shophouses. Apart from that, hopefully the service will be faster in preparing customer orders.

review_text: Tempat makan mie aceh favorite sudah hampir 8 tahun ansejak semester 1 kuliah Hampir semua makanan udah pernah saya coba dan semuanya enak sesuai sama lidah saya, sempet tanya juga sama temen ku yang orang aceh asli apakah yang disana juga rasanya sama kayak yang di bungoong jeumpa dan jawaban nya sih iyaaa Favorite masih dipegang mie aceh kuah daging pedas sama teh tarik nyaa(wanginya khas banget kayaknya lake cinnamon ya) Harga menurut ku worth it dengan porsi dan juga rasa yang enak, tapi memang waktu pertama kali kesini porsinya banyak banget sekarang tetap banyak tapi gak sebanyak dulu. Untuk suasana tempat makan nya, meja dan kursinya terbatas ygy dan memang rada panas juga kalau di cabang ciputat ini, kalau mau rada luas bisa ke yang di dekat stasiun jurangmangu. Kadang juga kalau lagi antri bisa makan waktu lebih dari 1 jam walupun take away. Last kalau kalian gak terlalu suka makanan yang banyak rempah dan bumbunya nendang bingbing pikirin dulu aja atau sharing bareng temen aja dulu
review_translated_text: Favorite place to eat Acehnese noodles for almost 8 years, since the first semester of college I have tried almost all the foods and they are all delicious according to my taste buds, I also asked my friend who is a native Acehnese whether what there tastes the same as the one at Bungoong Jeumpa and the answer is yes. The favorite is still the Acehnese noodles with spicy beef soup and the Teh Tarik (the smell is really distinctive, like lake cinnamon, right) In my opinion, the price is worth it with the portions and delicious taste, but when I first came here the portions were really big, now they are still big but not as much as before. As for the dining atmosphere, the tables and chairs are limited and its also a bit hot at the Ciputat branch, if you want a bit more space, you can go to the one near Panggangmangu station. Sometimes, if youre queuing, it can take more than 1 hour, even if its take away. Lastly, if you dont really like food with a lot of spices and kicking bingbing, just think about it or share it with friends first

review_text: Ini mie Aceh terenak yang pernah saya coba dari sekian banyak warung mie aceh di pulau jawa ini. Rasa bumbunya kaya akan rempah, medok khas bumbu aceh. Pernah tinggal 9 tahun di aceh dan mie ini benar2 otentik rasanya. Bagi yang tidak suka pedas jangan coba2 pesan yang pedas, karena pedasnya memang nggak kaleng2. Satu porsi mie goreng daging aceh cukup membuat kenyang. Dagingnya enggak pelit. Sekali kesini rasanya ingin kembali lagi. Sayang tempatnya terbatas dan harus rela gantian dengan pengunjung lainnya di kala pengunjung ramai. Tempat parkir untuk roda dua lumayan memadai, tapi untuk roda 4 memang agak susah, biasanya disepanjang jalan sebrang warung, tapi tenang saja ada juru parkir yang sigap mengarahkan kendaraan anda. Jangan lupa uang parkirnya.
review_translated_text: This is the tastiest Acehnese noodle I have ever tried from the many Acehnese noodle stalls on the island of Java. The taste of the seasoning is rich in spices, medok is a typical Acehnese spice. Ive lived in Aceh for 9 years and these noodles really taste authentic. For those who dont like spicy, dont try to order spicy, because it cant be spicy. One portion of Acehnese beef fried noodles is enough to make you full. The meat is not stingy. Once youve been here youll want to come back again. Unfortunately the space is limited and you have to be willing to change with other visitors when there are lots of visitors. Parking for two wheels is quite adequate, but for four wheels it is a bit difficult, usually along the road opposite the shop, but dont worry there are parking attendants who are ready to direct your vehicle. Dont forget the parking fee.

review_text: juara porsinya banyak banget level pedes ya beneran pedes, kalo ngga suka pedes mending pilih lv sedang (itupun masih pedes) kayanya lebih pedes mie aceh versi goreng daripada tumis. toppingnya banyak <<<333 untuk rasa enak bgt, mereka kaya punya rasa khas nya sendiri. nggabisa ditemuin di tempat lain. teh tariknya enak pls tempat oke cukup bersih dan nyaman buat dine in, parkirnya aja agak sempit tapi abang parkir sangat helpful duh semua oke gimana dong, udah jadi top of mind kalo bm mi aceh
review_translated_text: champion the portions are really big The spicy level is really spicy, if you dont like spicy its better to choose medium level (and even then its still spicy) It seems like the fried version of Acehnese noodles is spicier than the stir-fried version. lots of toppings <<<333 As for the delicious taste, they seem to have their own unique taste. cant be found anywhere else. the Teh Tarik is delicious pls The place is okay, quite clean and comfortable for dine in, the parking is a bit narrow but the parking guy is very helpful oops, everything is okay, how about it, its already top of mind when it comes to BM Mi Aceh

review_translated_text: The coffee is lacking, and the strawberry Choco is lacking. The tea has less sugar and is even bland. As for the aglio O lio, it doesnt seem like aglio O lio, but because I like spicy its delicious because spicy isnt suitable for small children/people who dont like spicy. For gohyong its not bad, but its a shame that the sauce has too much vinegar, so the tamarind vinegar is really too strong. Even though the atmosphere and crew are very good. Maybe why its quiet is because the quality and taste of the food and drinks need to be improved, because the price and taste are not worth it, and the +++ costs (service, tax, etc.) are too much. review_text: Jalan ke tempatnya bener bener hidden dan lucu. Lewat gang-gang kecil dan lucu. Tempatnya bener-bener ngingetin sama tahun 2018-2019 pas banyak kafe dengan tema tropis gitu wkwk. Dibuat serasa di bali dengan ornamen-ornamennya. Outdoornya luas banget, dan juga wangi wangi bunga. Lagunya juga indo pop 2018-2019, nostalgic banget rasanya. Dateng kesana ketika hari kerja sore. Kafenya ga crowded, malah cenderung sepi. Pas kesana cuma ada 2 orang di outdoor dan 1 orang di indoor. Sepi kaya gini, makanan dan minumannya cukup cepet dateng, sekitar 5-8 menit udah sampe. Pesen pancake dan iced latte mereka. Iced lattenya nothing special, cenderung biasa aja. Rasanya kurang balanced dan porsinya ga terlalu banyak, cuma worth the price. Harganya ga terlalu mahal. Yang mengecewakan sekali adalah pancakenya. Ada 3 pancake dan semuanya bau telur. Kayanya kurang vanili ya. Kalo malem, disini banyak banget nyamuk. Yah hati hati aja kalo outdoor dan pake celana pendek. Katanya sih ada live music setiap malam minggu.. yah worth to try kalo misalnya mau ke tempat nuansa bali
review_translated_text: The way to the place is really hidden and funny. Through small and cute alleys. The place really reminds me of 2018-2019 when there were lots of cafes with tropical themes, haha. Make it feel like youre in Bali with the ornaments. The outdoor area is very spacious, and it also smells of flowers. The song is also 2018-2019 Indo pop, it feels really nostalgic. Came there on a weekday afternoon. The cafe is not crowded, in fact it tends to be quiet. When I got there there were only 2 people outside and 1 person indoors. Its quiet like this, the food and drinks arrived quite quickly, they arrived in about 5-8 minutes. Order their pancakes and iced lattes. The iced latte is nothing special, just ordinary. The taste is not balanced and the portion is not too big, its just worth the price. The price is not too expensive. What was really disappointing was the pancakes. There were 3 pancakes and they all smelled of eggs. It doesnt seem like theres enough vanilla. At night, there are lots of mosquitoes here. Well, just be careful if you go outdoors and wear shorts. They say there is live music every night of the week... well its worth trying if for example you want to go to a place with a Balinese feel

review_text: Tempatnya bagus untuk kebutuhan instastory, makanan dan minumannya juga oke. Untuk harga juga masih standard kafe pada umumnya. Ada indoornya juga tapi ga terlalu besar. review_text: WORTH IT BANGET ASLI!!! coworking space per day per person only 50k yg didapet: wifi 12jam anti lemot (pake voucher gitu nanti tinggal connect), vibes yg TENAAANNGGG banget, gelang akses jadi ga sembarang orang masuk, colokan dimana2 setiap meja setiap tempat ada, dingin, kursi nyaman banget, ada tempat yg perbilik buat sendiri, meja panjang/bulet buat sharing (bisa sendiri juga), bisa pilih tempat di deket jendela buat liat view ciputat yg agak macet itu, SATU LAGIII, dengan harga segitu udah include 1 food/bevarages + 1 minuman random gratiss (pernah dapet you c 1000, air mineral, pocari). bisa seharian dari buka sampe tutup tanpa di tegor aku baru coba caramel latte sama tiramisu latte dan 2 2nya enakk ga terlalu manis, typical kopi yg aku suka. riceboxnya normal kaya instant food yg simple aja gitu ga banyak isian tp udah cukupp, aku lebih rekomendasiin dori sambel matah. dorinya banyak, sambelnya lebih enak menurutku dibanding sama sambel korek, dengan porsi nasi yg mengenyangkan. untuk french fries bisa lebih enak lagi harusnya, karena sayangnya dia pas masih panas udah di pack, jadi rasanya kaya ga renyah dan kaya melempem/? gitu, kurang enak dimakan :( toilet kalo siang ke sore emang agak kurang bersih yh dan cuma ada 2 bilik campur, jadi better bawa peralatan kaya tisu basah etc sendiri, karena lantai 1 dan 3 tuh rame, musholla ada kok tp kecil. JADI HARGA SEGITU UDAH DAPET TEMPAT SUPER PW, MAKANAN, DAN MINUMAN buat wfc, nugas, skripsian, udah tempat paling pas
review_translated_text: WORTH IT IS REALLY ORIGINAL!!! coworking space per day per person only 50k what you get: 12 hour non-slow wifi (use a voucher then just connect later), really TENAAANNGGG vibes, access bracelet so not just anyone comes in, plugs everywhere at every table, every place is available, cool, really comfortable chairs, there is a place to make your own cubicle, long/round table for sharing (you can do it yourself too), you can choose a place near the window to see the view of Ciputat which is a bit congested, ONE MORE, for that price it includes 1 food/bevarages + 1 free random drink (have you ever had one? c 1000, mineral water, pocari). You can go all day from opening to closing without being reprimanded I just tried caramel latte and tiramisu latte and both were delicious, not too sweet, typical coffee that I like. The rice box is normal, just like simple instant food, theres not a lot of filling but its enough, I recommend dori sambal matah. Theres a lot of dori, the chili sauce is tastier in my opinion than the lighter chili sauce, with a filling portion of rice. As for French fries, they should be even tastier, because unfortunately when theyre still hot theyre already packed, so they dont taste crispy and like theyre soggy/? I see, its not good to eat :( The toilets from midday to evening are a bit less clean and there are only 2 mixed cubicles, so its better to bring your own equipment like wet wipes, etc., because the 1st and 3rd floors are busy, there is a prayer room but its small. SO FOR THAT PRICE YOU GET A SUPER PW PLACE, FOOD AND DRINK For WFC, assignments, thesis, its the right place

review_translated_text: I have bought Acehnese noodles here several times... because of the hygienic belief, the delicious taste and the right level of doneness. Hopefully the quality can return to its original quality

review_text: kalau ke pasar lama pasti lewatin tempat ini tapi belum pernah cobain karena tujuannya makan bakso. kali ini ke pasar lama cobain juga. pesanan kami 1. Mie aceh tumis --> ini enak mienya rasa karinya medok banget mie nya juga dimasak pas gak kelembekan. bisa pilih level pedes juga dan ada acar bawangnya juga 2. nasi goreng --> pesen yg daging sapi rasanya biasa aja sih bumbu kurang medok kurang rasa 3. martabak aceh yg biasa --> ini kayak martabak telor telor tapi gak kayak yg martabak biasa pake kulit ya ini lebih berasa telornya ada cocolan kari 4. roti cane kuah kari --> rotinya gurih lembut bisa pilih yang manis juga pake susu atau coklat. ini kami pilih yg pake kari. kuah karinya rasanya agak asem ini gak tau ya apa rasanya emang gitu atau ... tempatnya open space gitu cuaca panas banget jadi gak nyaman meja berdebu dan ada asbak rokok di tiap mejanya gak nyaman jadinya pengen cepet2 kelar makan
review_translated_text: If you go to the old market you will definitely pass this place but have never tried it because the goal is to eat meatballs. This time, go to the old market and try it too. our order 1. Stir-fried Acehnese noodles --> these noodles are delicious, the curry flavor is really medok, the noodles are also cooked just right, theyre not soft. You can choose the spicy level too and there are pickled onions too 2. Fried rice --> ordered the beef, it just tasted normal but the spices werent medok and lacked flavor 3. Regular Aceh martabak --> this is like egg martabak but not like the regular martabak with skin, it tastes more like egg with curry sauce 4. Roti cane with curry sauce --> the bread is soft and tasty, you can choose sweet and also use milk or chocolate. We chose the one with curry. The curry sauce tastes a bit sour, I dont know whether it tastes like that or... the place is open space so the weather is really hot so its not comfortable the tables are dusty and there are cigarette ashtrays on each table its not comfortable so I want to finish eating quickly

review_text: Tempat makan yang enak dan nyaman untuk keluarga atau siapapun yang lagi laper. Saya pribadi cuma sempat pesan jus tomat disini yang rasanya seger, hanya saja seharusnya waktu itu saya pesan tanpa memakai gula biar lebih sehat. Sedangkan teman saya pesan nasi goreng aceh dengan telur dadar. Untuk yang kurang tahan makanan pedas, mungkin perlu request agar tidak terlalu pedas, mengingat makanan Aceh atau sekelasnya kebanyakan menggunakan bumbu dan rasa pedasnya yang sawadikap. Pesan di tempat duduk yang nanti akan diberikan list menu oleh pelayan. Sedangkan untuk membayar via kasir yang ada di depan dekat pintu masuk, belakangan setelah selesai makan.
review_translated_text: A delicious and comfortable place to eat for families or anyone who is hungry. Personally, I only ordered tomato juice here which tasted fresh, but I should have ordered it without sugar so it would be healthier. Meanwhile, my friend ordered Acehnese fried rice with omelet. For those who cant stand spicy food, you may need to request that it not be too spicy, considering that Acehnese food or its class mostly uses sawadikap spices and has a spicy taste. Order at your seat and the waiter will give you a menu list. Meanwhile, you can pay via the cashier at the front near the entrance, later after you finish eating.

review_text: Mie Aceh Garuda offers a delightful culinary experience with its flavorful dishes and aromatic coffee, accompanied by the warm hospitality of its staff. Nestled beside the main street, the ambiance can be lively and bustling, but for those who enjoy the energy of urban life, it only adds to the charm. Despite the hustle and bustle, it provides a cozy retreat where patrons can relax and savor their meals amidst the vibrant surroundings. The competitive pricing makes it accessible to all, while the iconic red chairs and tables evoke a sense of nostalgia, reminiscent of the streets of Aceh. Overall, Mie Aceh Garuda offers a unique dining experience that not only tantalizes the taste buds but also transports diners to the heart of Acehnese culture.

Layak didapuk sebagai hidden gem di seputaran Bintaro-Pamulang. T4nya adem, mayan compact tapi penataamnya oke. Cocok buat WFA atau ngerjain tugas, ada colokan tiap meja. Kalau mau meeting ada ruang ala perpustakaan yang bisa disewa per jam. Mas2 baristanya amat ramah, rajin menyapa, informatif dan sigap melayani. Nyobain capuccino dari beans lokal, rasanya   ok. Apple strudelnya yummy banget, renyah pastry dan saus apelnya pas. French friesmya agak lama keluarmya, ada cita rasa taburan rosemary. Merchandise storenya oke banget, desain dan kualitas barangnya mulai dari kaos, poster, sampe aneka pouch dan bag dari bahan daur ulang kemasan makanan kucing.
review_translated_text: Worthy of being lined up as a hidden gem around Bintaro-Pamulang. The T4 is cool, quite compact but the styling is okay. Suitable for WFA or doing assignments, there are plugs for each table. If you want to have a meeting, there is a library-style room that can be rented by the hour. The baristas are very friendly, diligent in greeting, informative and ready to serve. Try capuccino from local beans, it tastes ok. The apple strudel is really yummy, the pastry is crispy and the apple sauce is perfect. The French fries took a while to come out, they tasted like a sprinkling of rosemary. The store merchandise is really good, the design and quality of the goods range from t-shirts, posters, to various pouches and bags made from recycled cat food packaging materials.

review_text: Nuansa kafe yang cukup nyaman untuk keluarga, dengan sentuhan islami yang didukung oleh kutipan ayat suci serta pernak-pernik serupa. Untuk sisi pelayanannya sih memuaskan banget, karena para pegawainya sangat ramah dan gesit melayani pelanggan. Dari segi rasa kopinya menurut saya tidak ada yang istimewa, dan makanannya pun tidak berbeda jauh. Sayang ketika kemarin saya memesan fetuccini, tingkat kematangannya masih belum pas jadi agak keras. Walaupun begitu, masih cukup tertolong dengan singkong goreng dan mie nyemek alias indomie-nya yang enak. Wajar sih, karena harga yang ditawarkan pun tergolong terjangkau.
review_translated_text: The atmosphere of the cafe is quite comfortable for families, with an Islamic touch supported by quotes from holy verses and similar knick-knacks. In terms of service, it is really satisfying, because the employees are very friendly and agile in serving customers. In terms of the taste of the coffee, in my opinion there is nothing special, and the food is not much different. Unfortunately, when I ordered fetuccini yesterday, the level of doneness was still not right so it was a bit hard. Even so, it is still quite helpful with the delicious fried cassava and nyemek noodles, aka indomie. Its natural, because the price offered is quite affordable.

review_text: Dateng for the 1st time kesini sabtu jam 11, masih agak sepi. Tempatnya lumayan enak, kalau cerah bisa pilih outdoor ada area sitting bar untuk menyendiri sambil lihat pemandangan toll. Sayang pas hujan tampias, sebaiknya roof ditambahin. Karena kesini sm suami dan anak, pilih area indoor ber-AC yg adem. Pesan Mie karet ori dan pangsit rebus, karena pake ayam kampung   semua enak dan anak yg batuk jadi bs makan sehat & aman. Mienya kenyal dan ndut jd puas + worth the price. Mie dan pangsit rebus : 8,5/10. Hot Lemon Tea: 8/10 PakSu minum Japanese drip filtered coffee beans natural anaerob :8/10 ada asamnya tapi msh ada body. Kalau kesini lagi cocok pas lagi sepi spt ini. Apalagi hujan gerimis.. feels like home. Tapii kalau tempatnya lg rame mungkin cocok untuk eat&go aja. Pelayanan ramah dan baik barista & waiternya. Recommended? Yes. Visit Again? Yes.
review_translated_text: Came here for the 1st time, Saturday at 11, it was still a bit quiet. The place is quite nice, if its sunny you can choose the outdoor sitting bar area to be alone while looking at the view of the toll road. Unfortunately, when it rains, it would be better to add a roof. Because youre here with your husband and children, choose a cool, air-conditioned indoor area. Order original rubber noodles and boiled dumplings, because they use free-range chicken   everything is delicious and children who have coughs can eat healthily & safely. The noodles are chewy and ndut so Im satisfied + worth the price. Boiled noodles and dumplings: 8.5/10. Hot Lemon Tea: 8/10 PakSu drinks Japanese drip filtered coffee beans natural anaerobic : 8/10 there is acid but it still has body. If you come here again, its suitable when its quiet like this. Especially the drizzling rain... feels like home. But if the place is busy, maybe its suitable for eat&go. Friendly and good service from the baristas & waiters. Recommended? Yes. Visit Again? Yes.

review_text: Sengaja mampir ke sini di suatu siang. Sempat ragu untuk masuk ke dalam, karena terlihat sepi pengunjung. Tetapi akhirnya tetap memantapkan niat untuk makan di sini. Nuansa Jawa sangat kental ketika masuk dari pintu depan menuju ke area parkir di bagian belakang. Alunan musik dari berbagai daerah Indonesia terdengar ketika berjalan menuju area resto. Aku memilih meja luar di Joglo yang berhadapan langsung dengan taman depannya. Desain interior dan furniturenya segaja dipilih yang bertema lawasan tempo dulu. Masuk ke sini serasa masuk ke rumah eyang di desa jaman dulu. Cantik sebenarnya, hanya saja aku merasa agak sedikit suram suasananya. Mungkin karena hanya ada aku dan pasanganku, satu satunya pengunjung. Aku memilih menu rekomendasi dari mbaknya yang datang menghampiri dan melayani kami, Soto Betawi Campur. Dari aroma yang tercium sih udah kebaca, enak nih sotonya. Dan memang benar!! Soto Betawinya kaya bumbu, daging gak keras, seger banget. Jujurly pengen nambah sih, cuma perutnya yang gak muat.
review_translated_text: Accidentally stopped by here one afternoon. I was hesitant to go inside, because it looked empty of visitors. But in the end, I still decided to eat here. The Javanese feel is very strong when entering from the front door to the parking area at the back. Music from various regions of Indonesia can be heard when walking towards the restaurant area. I chose an outside table at Joglo which faced the front garden. The interior design and furniture were deliberately chosen to have an old era theme. Entering here feels like entering your grandfathers house in an old village. Its actually beautiful, its just that I feel the atmosphere is a bit gloomy. Maybe because there was only me and my partner, the only visitors. I chose the recommended menu from the lady who came over and served us, Soto Betawi Campur. From the aroma that I can smell, I can already tell that this soto is delicious. And its true!! Soto Betawi is rich in spices, the meat is not tough, its very fresh. Honestly, I want to add more, but my stomach doesnt fit.

review_text: Tempatnya beneran dapet kesan jawa kuno, gemes bgt buat prewedding, lamaran atau private wedding cocok sekali. Makannya gak gtu byk pilihan. Harga relatif mahal tapi rasanya lumayan enak kok terutama bebeknya enak. Recommended.
review_translated_text: The place really has an old Javanese feel, really lovely for pre-wedding, proposals or private weddings, perfect. There arent many choices for eating. The price is relatively expensive but the taste is quite good, especially the duck is delicious. Recommended.

SEMUA ENAK! canenya suka banget!! kopinya dua dua enak, both bold gt kopinya tp i like aren better sih. indomie bangladeshnya juga enak tp ga terlalu kentel bumbunya, saya coba campur pake kuah kari cane jadi endul hehe. total price 95k sajaa     next time mau coba mie aceh nyaa hihi definitely would go back
review_translated_text: Im just here for fun looking at the Aceh coffee banner, he said. interesting. For ambience, its just normal, but the menu is interesting at the Acehnese restaurant, the choice of coffee, some are manual, some are machine. I ordered palm coffee, Tarik coffee, beef curry cane, Bangladeshi Indomie. ALL DELICIOUS! I really like the cane!! Both coffees are delicious, both are bold, but I like arent better. The Bangladeshi Indomie is also delicious but the seasoning isnt too thick, I tried mixing it with cane curry sauce so it was delicious hehe. total price only 95k     next time I want to try Aceh noodles hihi definitely will go back

review_text: The most authentic Acehnese food Ive ever had. Being away from my homeland - Indonesia for so long, Im craving for the real, traditional, and true from the heart Acehnese food. This restaurant delivers all of that. The spices they use was original, the quality of raw materials used was top notch, and not to mention, the taste was impeccable. The owner, who we called Bang Ipun, pours his passion and pride into this establishment. To me, he delivers what he intended to do. No disappointment! Bravo to Tutue Kopi Aceh owners and crew, you did it!

Sepertinya belum banyak warga BSD yang tahu kalau ada kedai aceh yang enak disini. Pelayanan cepat dan memuaskan. Menu makanan sangat variatif dan minuman sangat beragam khususnya kopi. Saya suka menu mie bangladesh dan roti canai susu. Untuk kopi sangernya enak dan mirip rasanya waktu saya minum di Banda Aceh.
review_translated_text: It seems that not many BSD residents know that there is a delicious Acehnese shop here. Fast and satisfying service. The food menu is very varied and the drinks are very varied, especially coffee. I like the Bangladeshi noodle menu and milk roti canai. The sanger coffee is delicious and similar to the taste when I drank it in Banda Aceh.

review_text: The definition of where Ive been all this time, I just found a place to eat Acehnese noodles where the place is cozy and comfortable, and the food is delicious     I ordered Acehnese noodles, stir-fried egg, martabak, Bangladeshi indomie, shaved cucumber ice, everything was delicious! Definitely will come back again, still curious about the other menus!
Terimakasih bapak Ibu. Masakan mangat that. InsyaAllah kamo balek lom
review_translated_text: Thank you ladies and gentlemen. That delicious dish. God willing, well be back

review_translated_text: A comfortable, clean, cool place so you can stay for a long time while doing your work. This time try Acehnese noodles and egg martabak. It tastes good and fits. Affordable price. Usually when you meet someone selling Acehnese noodles, the room is hot and smells of cooking smoke, its comfortable here. Will come again to try other menus.

review_text: Pesan Mie tumis Aceh Udang + telur. Rasa rempahnya enaaakk sekali. Es kopi sangernya jg enak     pelayanan ramah. Tempatnya jg enak dan luas. Dapurnya didepan jd makan didlm gak kena bau masakan.

review_text: Sangat puas sama pelayanan yang ramah, makanannya luar biasa saya pesan mie aceh kuah daging, nasi goreng aceh daging, sama roti canai kari daging. Nasi gorengnya b aja sih cuma dagingnya itu gila enak bgt. Untuk mie aceh dagingnya kuahnya otentik bgt enak bgt. Terakhir roti canai kuah karinya belum ada lawan sih saat ini yang pernah saya makan. review_translated_text: Very satisfied with the friendly service, the food was extraordinary. I ordered Aceh noodles with meat sauce, Aceh meat fried rice, and meat curry roti canai. The fried rice is just the meat, its crazy and really delicious. For Acehnese noodles, the meat in the sauce is really authentic and really delicious. Lastly, there is no rival to the roti canai with curry sauce that I have ever eaten. The second visit still didnt disappoint, the boiled noodles were really good, and the canai wasnt rich in other places, it was crunchy, the aroma was really good, it was really good.

Masukan Anda sangat berarti bagi kami. Salam sehat selalu.
review_translated_text: This burger has just opened in the city of Tangerang, if its in Tangerang there are probably already many branches.
